data.a-minimal-behavior-pack-manifest#A minim:
{
  "format_version": 2,
  "metadata": {
    "product_type": "addon"
  },
  "header": {
    "name": "my-addon BP",
    "description": "Generated by create-mc-bedrock",
    "uuid": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
    "min_engine_version": [1, 21, 80],
    "version": [1, 0, 0]
  },
  "modules": [
    {
      "type": "data",
      "uuid": "22222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222",
      "version": [1, 0, 0]
    },
    {
      "type": "script",
      "language": "javascript",
      "entry": "scripts/main.js",
      "uuid": "33333333-3333-3333-3333-333333333333",
      "version": [1, 0, 0]
    }
  ],
  "dependencies": [
    {
      "module_name": "@minecraft/server",
      "version": "1.19.0"
    },
    {
      "uuid": "44444444-4444-4444-4444-444444444444",
      "version": [1, 0, 0]
    }
  ]
}
The last dependency entry is the cross-reference to the resource pack
(see below).

data.a-minimal-resource-pack-manifest#A minim:
{
  "format_version": 2,
  "metadata": {
    "product_type": "addon"
  },
  "header": {
    "name": "my-addon RP",
    "description": "Generated by create-mc-bedrock",
    "uuid": "44444444-4444-4444-4444-444444444444",
    "min_engine_version": [1, 21, 80],
    "version": [1, 0, 0]
  },
  "modules": [
    {
      "type": "resources",
      "uuid": "55555555-5555-5555-5555-555555555555",
      "version": [1, 0, 0]
    }
  ],
  "dependencies": [
    {
      "uuid": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
      "version": [1, 0, 0]
    }
  ]
}
Notice that the BP depends on the RP's header.uuid
(44444444-...), and the RP depends on the BP's header.uuid
(11111111-...). Each manifest names the other by UUID.

data.typescript-interface#TypeScript interfac:
interface BedrockConfig {
  /** Project name, used for .mcaddon filename and manifest header.name */
  name: string;
  /** Project version, used for .mcaddon filename */
  version: string;
  /** Pack source directories (relative to config file) */
  packs: {
    bp: string;  // default: "packs/BP"
    rp: string;  // default: "packs/RP"
  };
  /** TS entry point for the script module (relative to config file) */
  entry: string;  // default: "src/main.ts"
  /** Build output directory (relative to config file) */
  out: string;  // default: "dist"
  /** Deploy configuration */
  deploy: {
    target: "retail" | "custom";  // default: "retail"
    customPath: string | null;     // required when target === "custom"
  };
  /** Minecraft scripting API target version */
  minecraft?: {
    serverVersion?: string;  // e.g., "1.19.0", used for hints only, not enforced
  };
}

data.packs#packs:
Type: { bp: string; rp: string }
Required: no (defaults applied)
Default: { "bp": "packs/BP", "rp": "packs/RP" }
Source paths to the behavior and resource pack folders, relative to
the config file. Both directories must exist at build time and must
each contain a manifest.json.
"packs": {
  "bp": "packs/BP",
  "rp": "packs/RP"
}

data.complete-example#Complete example:
A full config with every field set explicitly:
{
  "name": "my-addon",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "packs": {
    "bp": "packs/BP",
    "rp": "packs/RP"
  },
  "entry": "src/main.ts",
  "out": "dist",
  "deploy": {
    "target": "retail",
    "customPath": null
  },
  "minecraft": {
    "serverVersion": "1.19.0"
  }
}
A minimal config relying on defaults:
{
  "name": "my-addon",
  "version": "1.0.0"
}
Both are valid. The second resolves to the same effective config as
the first.
